main event: An unidentified target was observed on radar for 9 minutes in the Pacific Ocean.
interesting points: The object was detected on radar but could not be visually acquired.
The radar signal was eventually lost and no positive identification could be made.
A commercial flight crew reported sighting an object traveling at high speed over the Pacific Ocean.
The object was described as a white light the size and shape of a faint star.
The object was observed traveling at an elevation of 30 degrees and a distance of 2 miles.
sighted object: unidentified target on radar, bright white light in the sky
